Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 8 (XINHUA) -- Some 50 foreign women 
experts gathered here today to mark the 84th anniversary of the 
International Women's Day. 
  Tian Shulan, a leading official of the All-China Women's 
Federation (ACWF), gave them a briefing on how Chinese women 
participate in economic construction and on the ACWF's efforts 
to expand international exchanges. 
  According to the State Bureau of Foreign Experts, some 1,500 
women experts from 30 countries now work in colleges as well as 
cultural, publication and news organizations throughout China. 

